Zlatan is set to headline his first concert in Lagos themed ‘Zlatan Live’ at the Balmoral Convention Centre, Federal Palace Hotel, Victoria Island Lagos on the 18th of December 2019. Temidayo Raphael Omoniyi popularly known as ZLATAN IBILE is a multitalented Nigerian born performing artiste. Zlatan Ibile is not only an indigenous rapper, singer and songwriter but also a dancer that originated one of the biggest dances in Africa; ZANKU. The event will be Zlatan’s first official concert as a headliner. He assures his fans and audience to excite then with his energetic Zanku moves, feature music performances to ensure it’s a night to remember for a long time. Ticket is already on sale on Nairabox. The Artiste has had an amazing year and it is only right to crown it all with a concert for his huge and loyal fan base. He is also the creator of the well-known slang ‘Kapaichumarimarichopaco’. Zlatan Ibile launched his talent and officially made his mark into the music industry in 2017. His songs; singles and collaborations continue to top various charts. With close 3 million active followers across his social media networks, Zlatan Ibile commands a speedy increase in fan base. Achievas Entertainment, one of Nigeria’s biggest show promoters will be promoting the event in collaboration with Zlatan’s Alleluyah Boyz Entertainment and they guarantee attendees of maximum entertainment and security.